install python versions via pyenv
pyenv install 3.6.5         # or other vers number
pyenv global 2.7.14         # or other vers number; default version

make project directory
>> mkdir projectname
>> cd projectname

create pipenv environment with version
>> pipenv --python 3.6.5

activate virtual environment
>> pipenv shell

install dependencies
>> pipenv install packagename

exit virtualenv
>> exit

set up pyenv as needed
in working directory:
>> pyenv local <version>
like:
>> pyenv local 3.6.5

https://jacobian.org/writing/python-environment-2018/

set up vim
set up github
test github

setting up git:
follow guide to set up SSH
use guide in new repository to view remote git operations
** need to make repository in web always
